   <head>EPIGRAM V.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="1" met="-+|--+|--+|--+" line_length="11">THO' cheerful, discreet, and with freedom well bred,</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|--+|--+|--+" line_length="11">She never repented an idle word said:</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|--+|--+|--+" line_length="11">Securely she smiles on the forward and bold,</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|--+|--+|--+" line_length="11">They feel what they owe her, and feel it untold.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
